{
  "texts": [
    "Liu et al. (2014) employed ELM to predict the large-scale soil moisture in Australian orchards.",
    "The results demonstrated that the model was capable of accurate forecasting.",
    "Support vector machine (Cortes and Vapnik, 1995) was proposed for applications in classification and regression.",
    "It aims to find the maximum-margin hyperplane that best separates sample points.",
    "To make this hyperplane more robust in high-dimensional feature spaces, SVM uses kernel functions to perform nonlinear mapping and create a new feature space where the data can be linearly separable."
  ]
}